{"DEME":[{"def":"A territorial subdivision of Attica (also of modern Greece), corresponding to a township.","pos":""},{"def":"An undifferentiated aggregate of cells or plastids.","pos":""}],"DEMEAN":[{"def":"To manage; to conduct; to treat.","pos":""},{"def":"To conduct; to behave; to comport; -- followed by the reflexive pronoun.","pos":""}],"DEMEANOR":[{"def":"Management; treatment; conduct.","pos":""},{"def":"Behavior; deportment; carriage; bearing; mien.","pos":""}],"DEMENCY":[{"def":"Dementia; loss of mental powers.","pos":""}],"DEMENT":[{"def":"To deprive of reason; to make mad.","pos":""}],"DEMENTATE":[{"def":"Deprived of reason.","pos":""}],"DEMENTATION":[{"def":"The act of depriving of reason; madness.","pos":""}],"DEMENTED":[{"def":"Insane; mad; of unsound mind.","pos":""}],"DEMENTIA":[{"def":"Insanity; madness; esp.","pos":""}],"DEMEPHITIZE":[{"def":"To purify from mephitic.","pos":""}],"DEMERGE":[{"def":"To plunge down into; to sink; to immerse.","pos":""}],"DEMERIT":[{"def":"That which one merits or deserves, either of good or ill; desert.","pos":""},{"def":"That which deserves blame; ill desert; a fault; a vice; misconduct; -- the opposite of Ant: merit.","pos":""}],"DEMERSED":[{"def":"Situated or growing under water, as leaves; submersed.","pos":""}],"DEMERSION":[{"def":"The act of plunging into a fluid; a drowning.","pos":""},{"def":"The state of being overwhelmed in water, or as if in water.","pos":""}],"DEMESMERIZE":[{"def":"To relieve from mesmeric influence.","pos":""}],"DEMESNE":[{"def":"A lord's chief manor place, with that part of the lands belonging thereto which has not been granted out in tenancy; a house, and the land adjoining, kept for the proprietor's own use.","pos":""}],"DEMESNIAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a demesne; of the nature of a demesne.","pos":""}]}